{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"05b66372-dce8-4183-9c39-cf37b952914b","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.com --tenant-id <id> --client-id <id>\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` if you need custom token validation. Run `dotnet new webapi --help` to see all available options for your SDK version.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"045c9446-6079-4617-9867-7c59fe1aafc1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to look at files.","outputTokens":310,"requestId":"A812:1D2ECE:CA2E21:E4A096:6A02791F"},"id":"84f48a72-11ce-4b32-b231-2e851d631b51","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:49:43.602Z","parentId":"66d771a6-fd8a-4b94-b6b0-95514c88040c"}
